@node Fortran90 code files cannot be compiled., Some packages from Octave--Forge's website cannot be installed., Limitations, Limitations
@unnumberedsec Fortran90 code files cannot be compiled.
Fortran90 and Fortran95 code files etc. cannot be compiled when using the command @command{mkoctfile} on the command line or when using the commands @command{mkoctfile} or @command{mex} in Octave. The reason is that the program @command{f2c} has been set up in Octave.app that can just convert Fortran77 code files into C--files. The generated C--files are then compiled with the command @command{gcc} that comes with your Apple's XCode Tools (Install these tools from 'DVD 1 of your Mac OS X Install Discs'). We've also added the script @file{fort77} to Octave.app that behaves like a Fortran compiler but in the background calls @command{f2c} and @command{gcc} automatically for you.

The @command{f2c} program is one of the smallest and oldest free Fortran converters/compilers available. Setting up another Fortran compiler that can compile Fortran90 and Fortran95 code files (eg. @command{g95 or gfortran}) for all the different versions of Apple's XCode Tools all the different versions of @command{gcc} is too difficult. We hope that @command{g95 or gfortran} somewhen becomes part of Apple's XCode Tools so that we do not need to set up @command{f2c} anymore. @* @*

@node Some packages from Octave--Forge's website cannot be installed., No spaces (and/or special characters) in the pathname before Octave.app are allowed., Fortran90 code files cannot be compiled., Limitations
@unnumberedsec Some packages from Octave--Forge's website cannot be installed.
Some of Octave--Forge's packages cannot be installed because of a missing @command{g95 or gfortran} command as described in the section before. Known packages that cannot be installed because they come with Fortran90 code files are
@itemize @minus
@item Main repository: @file{Optiminterp}
@item Nonfree packages: @file{Spline-gcvspl}
@end itemize

But if you find other bugs or other limitations in other packages of Octave--Forge then please report them to @email{octave-dev@@lists.sourceforge.net}. If you want to find out more information why the installation fails for a specific package then use the command @command{pkg install --verbose <package.tar.gz>} to build the package in verbose mode.

@node No spaces (and/or special characters) in the pathname before Octave.app are allowed.,  , Some packages from Octave--Forge's website cannot be installed., Limitations
@unnumberedsec No spaces (and/or special characters) in the pathname before Octave.app are allowed.
Do not install Octave.app in a place of your filesystem including spaces (and/or special character, eg. '&') in the pathname before Octave.app. Valid destinations eg. are 
@example
/Application/Octave.app
/Users/Me/Desktop/Octave.app
@end example
Not valid destinations including spaces and/or special character in the pathname eg. are
@example
/Applications/Other Apps/Octave.app
/Users/My Home/Desktop/Octave.app
/Users/Me&Others/Applications/Octave.app
/Users/Foo§13/Applications/Octave.app
@end example
If you set up Octave.app with a not valid pathname then this might result in different errors at startup or when already running Octave.app that normally cannot be reproduced.

