@unnumberedsubsec Can I upgrade Octave.app with binaries of the current Octave CVS?
Yes, the idea was to create a script file for Octave developers that compiles the current CVS sources of Octave and overwrites all binaries within Octave.app (eg. this way you can create a gdb--version of Octave). Carefully read the developer comments in the file @file{selfupdate.sh} from the Octave--Forge SVN before you try to update your Octave.app and also please keep the email traffic on the mailing--list @email{octave-dev@@lists.sourceforge.net} about "it doesn't work" small.

@node Are there any other Mac OS X Octave topics were I could help?,  , Can I upgrade Octave.app with binaries of the current CVS?, Developer FAQ
@unnumberedsubsec Are there any other Octave Mac OS X open topics were I could help?
Yes, in general the most Octave developers are subscribed to all of the Octave and Octave--Forge mailing--lists. You'll find there open threads and discussions abaout the ongoing work of Octave. Especially on the Mac OS X platform there are the following open topics:

@itemize
